    // Tools
    tool_regex_title: "Search and Replace (Regex)",
    tool_regex_desc: "Replace using regular expression",
    tool_regex_long_desc: "This tool is designed for the automatic searching and modification of text fragments based on specified rules. You can use it to process large lists of names, email addresses, or inventory numbers within your system. The main search rule is defined in a special search field where you describe the structure of the required data. If you need not only to find but also to replace the found parts, use the field for specifying a new value. This is very convenient when you need to bring all unique designations in event records to a single standard or hide confidential information. The tool supports the ability to ignore differences between capital and small letters, which significantly expands the search area. For this purpose, a setting is provided that disables sensitivity to character size. If your task consists only of extracting the necessary data, you can enable a mode to save exclusively found matches. In this case, all unnecessary parts of the source text will be discarded, and you will receive a clean list of results. This is useful when forming exports with only the required parts from complex reports. During the replacement process, you can use special references to found groups of characters to rearrange or supplement them. The entire process happens instantly right in the program window without sending data to third-party resources. You can experiment with search rules while immediately seeing the final processing result at the bottom of the window. The tool helps avoid routine manual work when editing hundreds of lines of textual information. Using such an approach guarantees high accuracy and repeatability of your data processing results. It is a reliable assistant for any specialist working with text settings or lists of system incidents.",
