    tool_dedup_title: "Remove Duplicates",
    tool_dedup_desc: "Keeps only unique lines",
    tool_dedup_long_desc: "This program block serves to clean lists of repeating elements and leave only unique lines. It is ideally suited for processing lists of usernames, mailing addresses, or device identifiers after merging several data sources. The block's operation begins with an analysis of each line of incoming text to identify exact matches. You can enable a preliminary cleaning of lines from extra spaces at the edges, which will ensure a more accurate comparison. This helps avoid situations where records that look identical at first glance are considered different due to invisible characters at the end or beginning. As a result of the work, you will receive a concise list where each element occurs exactly once. Such a tool is indispensable when preparing clean data for import into other accounting systems or for mailings. It allows you to significantly reduce the volume of processed information by removing unnecessary information noise. The mechanics of the operation are simple and do not require complex settings, providing a fast and predictable outcome. All transformations are performed on the fly, allowing you to immediately see how many extra records were removed from the general flow. The tool preserves the order of the first appearance of unique lines, which may be important for maintaining the sequence of events. Using this function prevents errors associated with multiple processing of the same information. It is a basic but extremely effective way to bring order to any text lists. The program guarantees the safety of your data since all processing takes place exclusively inside your browser. Data cleanliness and uniqueness are the key to the correct operation of any software.",
    tool_dedup_trim: "Trim spaces",

    tool_sort_title: "Sort",
    tool_sort_desc: "Sorts the list",
    tool_sort_long_desc: "This block is intended for ordering lines of text in accordance with the rules and logic you choose. You can use it to build alphabetical lists of employees, sort numerical performance indicators, or order event records by time. The tool offers several different operating modes to achieve the best result depending on the type of your data. The normal text mode simply compares characters with each other, which is suitable for most general tasks. The numeric mode allows for the correct processing of lists with digits so that the number ten comes after the number two, not before it. Smart sorting combines these approaches, correctly processing lines that contain both letters and digits simultaneously. You can choose the direction of ordering, arranging elements from start to finish or in reverse order. A setting is also available to ignore differences between capital and lowercase letters when comparing texts. This allows you to avoid a situation where words starting with the letter A end up in different parts of the list due to different cases. The result of the block's operation is always predictable and helps to quickly navigate through large volumes of information. Well-structured data significantly simplifies the search for needed records and the analysis of the overall picture. The entire process of rebuilding the list occurs instantly after changing any parameter. The tool supports working with regional language features, which guarantees the correct order of letters in the alphabet. Using automatic sorting saves a lot of time compared to manual arrangement of elements. This is an important stage in preparing any reports or system lists for further use.",
