    tool_reverse_title: "Reverse",
    tool_reverse_desc: "Reverses the list of lines",
    tool_reverse_long_desc: "This tool performs a simple but useful operation of completely changing the order of lines in your list to the opposite one. It is ideally suited for cases where you need to view the latest events in a record first or reverse the sequence of steps in an instruction. The block's work consists of making the very last line become the first, while the very first moves to the very end. No additional settings are required, as the logic of the action is as transparent and understandable as possible. You simply add this block to your processing chain, and it instantly reverses the current result. This is useful when working with system records that are appended to the end of a file, and you need to see the fresh information at the top. The tool does not change the content of the lines themselves but only rearranges them in the general list. Such an approach guarantees the safety of all data while changing its visual representation. The result of the work is visible immediately, allowing you to quickly assess the necessity of this action in the overall process. The mechanics of the operation are extremely efficient and handle lists of any size almost instantly. You can combine this block with other tools, for example, after sorting, to obtain the desired order. Simplicity of use makes this block accessible even to those who have never dealt with text processing. The absence of control parameters eliminates the possibility of error when configuring the block. This is a reliable way to quickly change the perspective on your textual data. Using list reversal helps in analyzing sequences and identifying patterns in data.",

    tool_compare_title: "Compare (Diff)",
    tool_compare_desc: "Compare incoming text with a second list",
    tool_compare_long_desc: "This block is designed for comparing the main text with a second list of data to identify common elements or differences. You can use it to check lists of permitted addresses, find new users, or remove already processed records. The second list for comparison is entered into a special text field inside the block's settings. For correct separation of elements in the second list, a choice of separator is provided, such as a new line or a comma. The main mechanics of the operation consist of choosing one of three result display modes. You can leave only those lines that are present in both lists simultaneously to find intersections. The difference search mode will show only those elements of the first list that are not in the second data set. A full display mode is also available, where each line is marked with a special symbol indicating its presence or absence in the lists. This allows you to clearly see the entire picture of relationships between two sets of textual information. The tool automatically removes extra spaces at the edges of lines before comparison to increase accuracy. Such an approach excludes errors caused by accidental inaccuracies during manual data entry. The entire matching process takes place on your device, which ensures the confidentiality of the compared lists. The result of the block's work allows you to quickly make decisions based on the analysis of correspondences. The tool is indispensable when preparing updates for data storages or checking access rights. Using automatic comparison guarantees the absence of omissions and errors typical of a human.",
