    tool_duplicates_title: "Find Duplicates",
    tool_duplicates_desc: "Shows only repeating lines",
    tool_duplicates_long_desc: "This tool helps to quickly detect and display only those lines that occur in your text more than once. It will be useful for system administrators to identify repeating login attempts or errors in configuration files. Instead of removing extra entries, this block, on the contrary, focuses your attention exactly on the problematic repetitions. In the settings, you can enable the display of the count of mentions for each found duplicate line. This allows you to immediately assess the frequency of occurrence of a particular event or the popularity of a certain value. If no repetitions are found, the tool will politely inform you about this with a special notification. The result of the work is a clean list of repeating elements with optional statistics for each of them. You can use this data for further investigation of the reasons for the appearance of redundant information in the system. The mechanics of the block's operation are based on a full scan of the entire incoming data array. Before analysis, the lines undergo preliminary processing to eliminate the influence of accidental spaces. The tool works very quickly even with very long lists, providing the result in fractions of a second. The visual representation of data in this block helps to focus on the most important things. Using the repeat search function is an important step in auditing and checking data integrity. You can easily integrate this block into your processing chain for regular monitoring of text quality. The program ensures full privacy since all calculations are conducted without transferring information to the network.",
    tool_duplicates_show_counts: "Show counts",
