    tool_filter_title: "Line Filter",
    tool_filter_desc: "Keep/Remove lines by condition",
    tool_filter_long_desc: "This program block allows you to filter out unnecessary lines from the general text based on a condition or keyword you set. You can use it to isolate only critical errors from a large event record or to search for employees by last name. The main parameter is the search text, which serves as a sample for checking each line. The tool offers several different ways of matching the text with your request. You can choose a simple inclusion mode, where the line remains if it contains the searched word in any of its parts. Options are also available for searching for lines that strictly start or end with a certain set of characters. If you need, on the contrary, to remove everything unnecessary, use the exclusion mode, which will delete all lines with the specified text. The entire filtering process occurs while ignoring the case of letters, which makes the search more flexible and convenient. At the bottom of the block, statistics are displayed on how many lines passed the check and how many were discarded. This helps to control the processing procedure and ensure the correctness of the settings. The result of the work is an updated list containing only the information you are interested in. The tool is indispensable when working with huge arrays of textual data where manual search is impossible. Simplicity of parameter configuration allows you to instantly switch between different filtering conditions. You can sequentially apply several such blocks to create complex data selection conditions. Using an automatic filter significantly increases the speed of working with text reports and lists.",
    tool_filter_query: "Search text",
