    tool_csv_title: "CSV Parser",
    tool_csv_desc: "Convert CSV to text by template",
    tool_csv_long_desc: "This tool is intended for converting data from table formats with separators into ordinary coherent text according to your own template. It is ideally suited for creating beautiful reports from accounting system exports, forming letters, or lists of settings. The main parameter here is the choice of the character that separates columns in your source text, most often a semicolon or a comma. You can configure the block to skip the first line if it contains only column headings. The most interesting part of the work consists of creating a template where you specify exactly how the data from the columns should be located. In the template, special designations are used to insert the content of the first, second, or any other column. For example, you can write a phrase into which the username and their email address from each row of the table will be automatically substituted. The tool takes each line in turn, breaks it into parts, and assembles a new sentence according to your rules. As a result, you receive a list of ready-made texts formed based on structured information. This eliminates the need to manually rewrite data from tables into text documents. The mechanics of the block's operation are very efficient and allow processing thousands of lines in a matter of moments. You immediately see the result of the conversion and can easily adjust the template to achieve the desired look. The tool supports the use of any characters in the template, including punctuation marks and spaces. Using such a converter guarantees uniformity and the absence of typos in all created records. This is a powerful means for automating routine preparation of text documents based on data storages.",
    tool_csv_delimiter: "CSV Delimiter (; or ,)",
