    tool_case_title: "Case",
    tool_case_desc: "UPPERCASE, lowercase, Capitalize",
    tool_case_long_desc: "This block serves for quickly changing the way letters are written in your text, making them capital or lowercase. You can use it to bring a list of names to a single standard or for preparing headings in documentation. The tool offers four different transformation modes to choose from depending on your current task. The first mode turns absolutely all letters into capital ones, which is often required for highlighting important warnings or codes. The second mode, on the other hand, makes all letters small, which is useful for uniformity of email addresses or system paths. The third option automatically makes the first letter of each sentence large, correcting possible inaccuracies during fast text entry. The fourth mode capitalizes each individual word, which is ideal for formatting names, surnames, or job titles. The mechanics of the block's operation are extremely simple: it takes each line and applies the chosen transformation rule to it. All changes occur instantly, and you immediately see the updated text in the program window. This eliminates the need to manually switch layouts or correct the case in each line individually. The tool correctly works with letters of different alphabets, maintaining the correctness of writing all characters. Using automatic case switching helps make your lists and reports more professional and neat. You can easily cancel or change the chosen mode if the result did not satisfy you. This block is an important element in the chain of preparing texts for publication or entry into data storages. Regular use of such a tool significantly reduces the time for preparing texts for further work. It is a simple and effective way to achieve visual cleanliness and order in any textual information.",
    tool_case_upper: "UPPERCASE",
