    tool_join_and: " and ",

    tool_split_title: "Split String",
    tool_split_desc: "Splits lines by delimiter",
    tool_split_long_desc: "This tool performs the operation opposite to merging, turning one or several lines into a long list of elements. It is ideally suited for cases where you have a line of words separated by commas and you want each word to stand on its own separate line. The main and only parameter here is the choice of the separator character by which the program will cut your text. You can use standard marks, such as a comma, a semicolon, or a space, and also set any unique character of your own. The mechanics of the block's operation consist of searching for all specified separators and creating a new line at the place of each such mark. As a result, instead of dense text, you receive an ordered column of data, which is much more convenient to analyze or sort. The tool automatically counts how many new lines were obtained in total and outputs this number in the statistics block. This is very useful when parsing complex system paths, parameter lists, or data copied from table cells. The separation process occurs instantly, allowing you to immediately proceed to the next stage of processing the obtained list. The split block is often the initial link in a chain of tools, preparing data for filtering or removing duplicates. The absence of extra settings makes working with it simple and error-free for any level of preparation. Using this tool guarantees neat separation of information without losing important text fragments. You can be sure of the accuracy of the result since the program strictly follows the separation rule you set. The number of lines at the output can significantly increase, which will clearly show the volume of your data. This is a basic block for turning solid text into a structured list of elements.",

    tool_add_line_title: "Add Line",
    tool_add_line_desc: "Adds lines to the beginning, end of the list and/or between lines",
    tool_add_line_long_desc: "This block allows for supplementing your list with new lines in specific places: at the very beginning, at the very end, or between each existing line. It is very useful when you need to add headings to a list, insert separation lines, or empty lines to improve readability. The tool has three independent fields for entering the text you want to add to the corresponding positions. You can fill any of them or all at once, creating the desired structure for your text document. Text from the field for the start of the list will be added once before the first line of source data. The content of the field for intervals will be inserted after each line of your list except for the very last one. The text for the end of the list will, accordingly, appear at the very final of the total result. The mechanics of the work consist of simple and predictable appending of your phrases to the general array of information. This is significantly more convenient and faster than manually inserting empty lines or marks in a text editor. The result of the work is visible immediately, which allows for easy adjustment of the added lines to achieve the ideal look. The tool does not analyze the content of your data but only expands the list according to the specified rules. Such an approach makes it a universal assistant for formatting any text reports or task lists. Using this block helps give your data a finished and professional look without extra effort. You can use this tool to create complex text structures simply by combining different entry fields. The program ensures neat and uniform addition of lines throughout the document. This is an excellent way to structure information for a presentation or further processing.",
    tool_add_line_start: "First line",
