    tool_template_title: "Templatizer (Nunjucks)",
    tool_template_desc: "Generation by template (body and lines available)",
    tool_template_long_desc: "This tool is intended for creating complex text documents and reports based on your data list and a special sample. It allows for turning a simple set of lines into full-fledged program code, an HTML page, or a detailed letter. You create a template in which you use special commands to insert data from your list into the required places. The tool supports cycles, allowing for the multiple repetition of certain parts of text for each line from your set. This opens up huge opportunities for automating the creation of same-type documents with different data. The mechanics of the work are based on the use of a popular and powerful template language that understands conditions and logical rules. For example, you can output information differently depending on the content of a line or its sequence number. As a result of the block's work, you receive a ready-made structured text formed strictly according to your rules. This eliminates the need to manually copy and paste data into complex text forms. The statistics block will show the total length of the resulting text, helping to control the volume of the final document. If an error is made in your template, the program will definitely point to it for quick correction. The tool is ideally suited for system administrators and developers who need to quickly generate configurations or documentation. All the magic of turning data into text happens right in your browser without using external resources. You can create an unlimited number of formatting variants for the same source data. This is a professional means for turning raw information into ready-to-use documents. Your work will become much more efficient thanks to the automation of the text formation process.",
    tool_template_tpl: "Nunjucks template (body and lines available)",

    tool_js_function_title: "Function (JS)",
    tool_js_function_desc: "Custom JS code for each line processing",
    tool_js_function_long_desc: "This tool provides almost unlimited possibilities for text processing by writing a small fragment of code in a popular programming language. It is intended for those situations where standard blocks are not enough and it is required to implement your own unique transformation logic for each line. You enter processing rules in a special field where each line of your list is represented as a variable. The tool applies your code to each line in turn, allowing for changing its content, conducting complex calculations, or changing the structure. For example, you can write a rule for extracting certain characters, changing encoding, or performing mathematical operations with numbers in the text. The mechanics of the block's operation ensure the isolation of your code for security, performing all actions exclusively inside the program. If a syntax error is made in the written rule, the statistics block will immediately inform you about this for making corrections. You can see the result of processing each line in real time, which allows for quick debugging of your logic. This tool is a powerful means for advanced users wishing to fully control the data transformation process. It allows for combining complex conditions and algorithms in one place without the need to use external editors. The result of the work is a completely changed list of lines according to your individual algorithm. Using this block makes your data processing chain maximally flexible and adaptive to any tasks. You can save your developments and use them repeatedly for solving similar automation tasks. This is the highest degree of control over textual information in your hands. The program guarantees the stability of your code execution within the specified processing parameters.",
    tool_js_function_code: "Function code (argument 'line')",
    tool_js_function_compilation_error: "Compilation error: ",

    tool_shuffle_title: "Random Shuffle",
    tool_shuffle_desc: "Shuffles lines in random order",
    tool_shuffle_long_desc: "This program block is intended for shuffling the lines of your list in an absolutely random, unpredictable order. You can use it to create random testing queues, shuffle answer choices, or for anonymizing the order of entries in records. The main parameter of the block is a special numeric value that serves as a seed for the random number generator. This allows you to obtain the same shuffling variant when using the same number, which is important for repeatability of results. If you leave the field empty or press the update button, the program itself will choose a new random number for the current session. The mechanics of the block's work guarantee that each line will remain in the list but will change its position to a new one. As a result, you receive the same data set but in a completely different, chaotic arrangement. The tool works instantly even with very large lists, providing high-quality shuffling of elements. Such an approach excludes any bias when choosing the order of lines by a human. The block does not have complex settings, which makes its use as simple and understandable as possible. You immediately see the new line order and can easily generate another sequence with one click. This is an excellent way to introduce an element of randomness into the processing of your textual data for various system tasks. Using automatic shuffling saves time and guarantees fairness in the distribution of elements in the list. You can use the obtained random order for conducting fair draws or distributing tasks among employees. The program ensures high speed of work and full unpredictability of each new variant of line rearrangement. Your information remains intact; only its visual representation changes.",
    tool_shuffle_seed: "Seed (number)",

    tool_to_hex_title: "To HEX",
    tool_to_hex_desc: "Convert text to hexadecimal code",
    tool_to_hex_long_desc: "This tool turns your text into a sequence of special codes that are directly understandable to computer equipment. Each letter or symbol is converted into a unique number in the hexadecimal numeral system, which is often used for low-level data analysis. The block offers a choice of several different encodings, such as modern world standards or old system character tables. You can choose a convenient result display format: a solid line, separated by spaces, or in the form of a detailed technical report. In the technical report mode, the text is broken into blocks of sixteen bytes with an indication of their address in memory and visual confirmation. The ability to enable a mode for displaying letter equivalents next to the codes is also available to simplify the search for the needed information. To improve readability, you can switch the case of letters in the codes between capital and lowercase. The mechanics of the work consist of the sequential encoding of each sign according to the chosen rule and its representation in digital form. This is indispensable for programmers and security specialists when studying the structure of files or data transmitted over the network. The tool correctly handles even complex symbols that may be displayed incorrectly in regular editors. The entire conversion process occurs instantly, allowing for quickly obtaining a digital snapshot of your text. Using this block guarantees an accurate representation of data in the form in which the computer system sees it. You can use this data for deep analysis or for insertion into technical documentation for your project. This is a professional means for those who want to look under the hood of textual information and understand its real structure. The program ensures high accuracy and support for many data representation standards.",
