    tool_from_hex_title: "From HEX",
    tool_from_hex_desc: "Convert hexadecimal code back to text",
    tool_from_hex_long_desc: "This program block performs the reverse operation, turning hexadecimal numeric codes back into human-understandable text. You can use it to decipher system records, analyze data from memory, or restore information from technical reports. The main parameter is the choice of encoding that was used when creating these codes so that letters and symbols are displayed correctly. The tool is very smart and supports various input data formats: from simple sequences of numbers to complex reports with addresses and marks. The program automatically cleans the incoming text from extra spaces, headings, and service characters before starting decoding. If errors or invalid signs are found in the codes, the statistics block will immediately point to the problematic line. The mechanics of the work consist of converting every two characters of the code into one byte of information and then assembling entire words from them. This eliminates the need to manually translate digits into letters according to character tables. The result of the work is the restored source text, divided into lines for ease of reading. The tool ensures high accuracy of deciphering even in the presence of extra technical information in the codes. You can easily experiment with different encodings if the first result turned out to be unreadable. Using this block significantly speeds up work on analyzing low-level data and restoring information. All processing occurs securely inside your browser. You will receive a clean and understandable text even from the most confusing sets of technical digits. This is a reliable bridge between machine code and human perception of information.",
