    tool_from_hex_error: "Decoding error: ",

    tool_encode_title: "Encoding (Base64/URL)",
    tool_encode_desc: "Encoding and decoding (Base64, URL)",
    tool_encode_long_desc: "This tool is designed for converting your text into special formats that are safe for transmission over the internet or storage in data storages. It supports two of the most popular information processing methods: Base64 and URL encoding. The first method turns any text into a set of standard Latin letters and digits, which is often used for transmitting attachments in emails or hiding data. The second method replaces special characters and spaces with codes using percentages so that links to websites work correctly and without errors. In the block's settings, you choose the desired action: encoding to protect the text or decoding to return to the original look. The mechanics of the work are based on standard algorithms that guarantee compatibility of the result with all modern systems. If an error occurs during the processing (for example, when attempting to decipher incorrect data), the tool will report this in the list of results. The entire conversion process occurs lightning fast, allowing for the processing of entire lists of lines at once. This eliminates the need to use scattered online services and ensures the confidentiality of your information. The result of the block's work is clean text in the chosen format, ready for use in your projects. Using this tool is an important step when preparing data for web development or system integration. Simplicity of switching between modes makes the block very convenient for quick verification and correction of different encoding formats. You can be sure that your data will be transmitted without distortion and loss to any point of the global network. This is a reliable means for ensuring compatibility of your textual data with any external standards. Regular use of such a converter helps avoid many problems with displaying special characters. You receive a guaranteed correct result suitable for any network protocols.",
    tool_encode_mode: "Action",
    tool_encode_error: "Error: ",

    tool_hash_title: "Hashing",
    tool_hash_desc: "Calculates CRC32, MD5, SHA-1, SHA-256, SHA-384, SHA-512",
    tool_hash_long_desc: "This tool serves for creating unique digital fingerprints of your text using special mathematical algorithms. Such a fingerprint allows for uniquely identifying a data line without disclosing its content, which is critically important for security and checking integrity. You can use this block for generating checksums of files, creating secure keys, or checking passwords. The tool offers a wide choice of different algorithms: from fast and simple to maximally reliable and modern ones. The mechanics of the work consist of applying the chosen mathematical function to each line of your list individually. As a result, for each data element, you receive a fixed sequence of characters that will change beyond recognition even with the change of one letter in the source text. This makes hashing an ideal means for detecting any, even the most insignificant, changes in information. The statistics block will inform you about the progress of operations and warn if additional libraries are required for work. All calculations are conducted locally on your computer, which guarantees absolute privacy of your source data. Obtained fingerprints cannot be turned back into text, which is an important property for protecting confidential information. The tool works very quickly, allowing for instantly obtaining results for large lists of lines. Using this block is standard practice when auditing system security and developing reliable software. You can be sure that your data is under the reliable protection of modern cryptographic methods. The program ensures accuracy and repeatability of hash codes for any textual information. It is your personal tool for ensuring digital hygiene and data security.",
    tool_hash_algorithm: "Algorithm",
    tool_hash_lib_error: "CryptoJS library not loaded! Check internet connection.",

    tool_debug_title: "Debug View",
    tool_debug_desc: "Visualizes invisible characters (spaces, tabs, breaks)",
    tool_debug_long_desc: "This special tool is intended for visualizing invisible characters and detailed study of the structure of your text. It is indispensable in cases where the text looks correct but programs output errors due to hidden spaces, tabs, or incorrect line breaks. The block replaces all invisible signs with special graphic symbols that clearly show their presence and type. You can separately enable and disable the display of dots for spaces, arrows for tab signs, and special marks for line endings. In addition, the tool allows for adding line numbering, which significantly facilitates the search for problematic places in large documents. The mechanics of the block's work consist of creating a temporary visual representation of your text while preserving its source content. In the statistics block, a detailed report is output on the number of found spaces and tabs in the entire data array. This helps to quickly assess text quality and make a decision on the necessity of its cleaning. The debugging result is displayed in a convenient preview window, where each character type is highlighted with its own color for better perception. You can use this tool as a final check before saving an important configuration or sending data to another system. Simplicity of settings allows for instantly switching between different visualization modes. Using this block helps avoid annoying errors caused by the human factor or the specifics of copying texts between different editors. Clean and correctly structured text is the key to the successful operation of any information system. The program provides you with a powerful magnifying glass for the most thorough analysis of every letter in your data. You will receive a full understanding of the inner life of your text and will be able to correct all hidden flaws.",
